=========================================================================

This software receives Bitcoin SV (BSV) transaction frames over UDP or TCP,
derives an IPv6 multicast group address from the transaction ID, and
retransmits each frame to all subscribers of the corresponding multicast
group across one or more configured egress interfaces.

=========================================================================
Conceptual Attribution

The IPv6 multicast transaction broadcast architecture from which this
software draws inspiration was articulated by Dr. Craig S. Wright:

  Multicast within Multicast: Anycast
  https://singulargrit.substack.com/p/multicast-within-multicast-anycast
  https://singulargrit.substack.com/

=========================================================================
Third-Party Standards

The v1 wire-frame format (FrameVerV1 = 0x01) accepted and forwarded by this
software transports transactions conforming to BRC-12: Raw Transaction
Format, a published standard maintained by BSV Blockchain:

  BRC-12: Raw Transaction Format
  BSV Blockchain Standards Repository
  https://github.com/bitcoin-sv/BRCs/blob/master/transactions/0012.md

